answer: mad concept, but how about instead of you taking the moral high ground and you making the choice of who ‘deserves’ brienne, you leave that choice to her?

summary: Indeed, dragons eat anything they want
title: Indeed, dragons eat anything they want
body:
Indeed, dragons eat anything they want

I have a dragon in my office. Not a real one. I wish I had a real one. First, I suppose they would have to exist. But it would be so awesome to have a fierce, colorful dragon to call my own. And, to set upon my haters. I’m joking.

In my office my dragon is perched on the corner of my desk next to my guests’ chair. Many people look at it. A few have asked me why I have that. Many will actually…

summary: Seriously has the dragonglass mining just started or is Danaerys at the very least contributing that? She brought a huge army...
question: Seriously has the dragonglass mining just started or is Danaerys at the very least contributing that? She brought a huge army and two gluttonous dragons without bringing her own stores of food. Did Danaerys talk about potentially getting more food from Dragon's Bay? Textiles? Literally anything that will help the North. Because she has been costing a lot of resources and there hasn't been an efficient return on "investment" that I've been able to see.
answer: i think they brought dragonglass with them (at least i hope so. gendry’s scene might have involved dragonglass. i wish i paid attention) but you’re absolutely right. besides an army and two dragons what has dany brought with her? usually i wouldn’t care (i’m not one of those blogs that is freaking out about the dothraki) but given that dany’s presence is going to cause a famine i have the same questions as you. like i said no one knows when winter will end, the most fertile region the north has ties to has been destroyed by the lannisters and dany burnt 1000 wagons of food from the reach meaning that whatever is left won’t be shared with the other kingdoms. even if winter ends the moment the night king is shattered, the north isn’t fertile and it will take a while to get a significant harvest. the rate at which the dragons are consuming livestock and the sheer size of dany’s army will cause a famine whether dany and her stans want to admit it or not

summary: Gendry and Arya had more chemistry in one scene than all of the jonerys scenes combined tbh. What do you think of Gendrya?
question: Gendry and Arya had more chemistry in one scene than all of the jonerys scenes combined tbh. What do you think of Gendrya?
answer:
jon had more chemistry with a cgi dragon.


I actually really love gendrya, I love gendry and Arya as characters and I think they are so cute together. Gendrya is really the only other couple I ship other than braime and I actually think they will be the two couples left to have a life at the end of the show. Maisie and Joe have insane chemistry and I think they’ve had development since way back in s1 so having their characters end up together would be a great end to their arcs
